FBIS4-43579 "drweu118_j_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-118 Daily Report 19 Jun 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Previti Cautious on Sending Troops to Rwanda Previti Cautious on Sending Troops to Rwanda LD1906183194 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 1745 GMT 19 Jun 94 LD1906183194 Rome RAI Due Television Network Italian BFN [Text] Italy is the European country that has said most clearly that it is ready to intervene in Rwanda, but on condition that the intervention is not a unilateral or multilateral one, but it takes place under an international umbrella. Here is Defense Minister Cesare Previti: [Begin Previti recording] We can take part in international humanitarian and peace operations. If we reach agreement to do something, we are ready and we have already said so. Reaching the agreement is the problem. We have tried to speed things up through the WEU [Western European Union]; there will be another meeting on Tuesday [21 June]. The French are insisting on a unilateral operation in which we have no intention of taking part, I believe. [end recording]
